          "name": "How many dunning letters are sent before an overdue account is escalated?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A standard dunning cycle runs three to four letters: a soft reminder around seven days past due, a firmer notice at 30 days, a final demand at 60 days, and escalation to legal or agency action after 90 days. Each letter restates the invoice number, amount, due date and interest claimed, so the trail supports later recovery."
          }
